# UI Rules

## Stack

Tailwind CSS + Shadcn UI. Design extracted from `Sample_Platform_Demo` HTML.

## Color Tokens

| Token | Hex | Usage |
|-------|-----|-------|
| cream | `#F6FAF9` | Page background |
| cream2 | `#EDF4EF` | Secondary bg |
| blue | `#2F7E96` | Primary CTA, links |
| blue-deep | `#235F73` | Hover states |
| blue-soft | `#E7F2F2` | Highlights |
| green | `#5E8E74` | Success, badges |
| green-deep | `#4A7560` | Ticker, accents |
| ink | `#1F3A43` | Body text |
| ink-soft | `#5A7077` | Muted text |
| line | `#DCE8E6` | Borders |

Define in `tailwind.config` — reference via `bg-cream`, `text-ink`, etc.

## Typography

- **Display:** Poppins (headings) — `font-display`
- **Body:** Mulish — `font-body`
- Eyebrow: `text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-blue`
- Section heading: `text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight`

## Spacing & Layout

- Max content width: `max-w-[1120px]` (`.wrap`)
- Section padding: `py-14` (54px)
- Card radius: `rounded-2xl` (16–18px)
- Button radius: `rounded-full`

## Component Inventory

Build these from HTML before pages:

**Primitives:** Button (primary/ghost/block), Input, Label, Card, Badge, Modal, Tabs, Accordion

**Layout:** Navbar (sticky), Footer, Sidebar, PageHeader, Ticker

**Marketing:** Hero, TrustBar, StepsGrid, PricingTiers, TestimonialCard, FAQ, CaptureForm, Band CTA

**Dashboard:** PlanBadge, ProgressBar, CourseCard, VideoCard, LessonList, EmptyState

**Commerce:** ProductCard, EnrollBox, CheckoutSummary, Invoice

**Admin:** DataTable, AdminForm, StatusBadge, UploadZone

## Shadcn Usage

- Use Shadcn for interactive primitives; style with project tokens.
- Extend via `className` and variants — don't fork component source heavily.
- `cn()` utility for conditional classes.

## Responsive

- Mobile-first.
- Grids: `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3`
- Hero: stack on mobile, side-by-side on `lg:`

## States

Every interactive UI needs: default, hover, focus, disabled, loading, error, empty.

## Anti-patterns

- No inline `style={{}}` — use Tailwind.
- No hardcoded hex in components — use theme tokens.
- No business logic in UI components.
- Mock data OK during UI sprint; label clearly as placeholder.
